# Limite dos países

Baixando os limites dos países.


```r
data(countries110, package = "rnaturalearth")
```

Convertendo pro formato `sf` e definindo SRC. 


```r
countries <- countries110 %>% 
  st_as_sf() %>% 
  st_transform(crs = 4326) %>% #4326 = WGS84, 4674 = SIRGAS2000
  clean_names()

# countries <- ne_countries(
#   type = "tiny_countries",
#   returnclass = "sf"
# )
```


```r
countries %>% 
  dplyr::select(brk_name) %>% 
  filter(
    grepl("Herz", brk_name)
```

# Unificando países com nomes difíceis

```r
guesses <- guesses %>% 
  mutate(
    pais = recode(
      .x = pais, 
      "Bosnia and Herzegovina" = "Bosnia and Herz.",
      "Eswatini" = "eSwatini",
      "Congo" = "Republic of the Congo"
    )
  )
```


Unificando a variável `chutes` com o limite dos países. Não existe o país `Malta`.


```r
(starting <- countries %>% 
   clean_names() %>% 
   dplyr::select(
     type, 
     admin, 
     brk_name, 
     formal_en, 
     note_brk,
     name_en,
     name_pt
   ) %>%
   # filter(name_en == "Guyane")
   inner_join(
     guesses,
     by = c("brk_name" = "pais")
   )
)
```

Encontrar o centróide de cada país*.* Não se aplica ao `USA`.


```r
(centers <- starting %>% 
  st_make_valid() %>% 
  st_centroid()
)
```

# Visualização do mapa


```r
(test <- leaflet() %>% 
   addTiles() %>% 
   addPolygons(
     data = starting,
     # fillColor = ~color,
     stroke = FALSE,
     opacity = 1,
   ) %>%
   addMarkers(
     data = centers
   )
 )
```

# Gerando o raio


```r
circles <- centers %>% 
  dplyr::select(name_en, brk_name, distancia, direcao, geometry) %>% 
  st_buffer(
    dist = centers$distancia*1000
  ) %>% 
  st_cast(
    "LINESTRING"
  )
```

```
## Warning in st_cast.sf(., "LINESTRING"): repeating attributes for all
## sub-geometries for which they may not be constant
```

# Mapa+Raio


```r
leaflet() %>% 
  # addTiles() %>% 
  addProviderTiles(
    # "Esri.WorldImagery" #Imagem de satélite
    "OpenStreetMap.Mapnik" #OpenStreetMap -> Software livre
  ) %>% 
  addPolylines(
    data = circles,
    # color = ~brk_name,
    popup = ~brk_name
  ) %>% 
  addMarkers(
    data = centers
  )
```

```r
  st_intersection() %>% 
  filter(
```

# Zoom na área


```r

  addTiles() %>% 
  addCircles(
    data = overlaps
  ) %>% 
  # 100km search area
  addPolylines(
    data = overlaps %>% st_buffer(dist = 100*1000)
```
